==English==
===Etymology===
''[[whoop]]'' (sound) + ''[[-ing]]'' + ''[[cough]]''; from the characteristic sounding cough that is a major symptom
===Noun===
'''whooping cough'''

# {{pathology}} A [[contagious]] [[disease]] of the [[respiratory system]] that usually affects [[children]]; caused by the [[bacterium]] ''[[Bordetella pertussis]]''. In the advanced stage it is characterised by spasms of [[cough]]ing followed by a whooping sound during the intake of breath.

